        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:49PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 448 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Dona Ana. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dona Ana, Leasburg, northern Las Cruces, and Jornada Range.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 1 and 2, and
between mile markers 6 and 15.
Highway 70 in New Mexico between mile markers 150 and 156.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
